headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson scores 28, Golden State runs away in 2nd half to top Miami 113-92

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Staring at a double-digit deficit midway through the fourth quarter without LeBron James available, Austin Reaves and the Los Angeles Lakers faced a clear choice.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reaves' triple-double, tiebreaking 3 helps rally Lakers past Bucks in 2OTs without LeBron James

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — The Oklahoma City Thunder lost a 20-point, second-half lead, but not their composure.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams scores 26, Thunder rally to top the Pelicans 119-112 after losing a 20-point lead

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 26 of his 28 points in the first half and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Sacramento Kings 132-96 on Tuesday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 28, Mavericks rout Kings 132-96
